-- 
Pao de Acucar, Cyrela Form Real Estate Partnership, Estado Says

-- B y   K a r e n   E e u w e n s
-- 
2011-09-23T11:52:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/pao-de-acucar-cyrela-form-real-estate-partnership-estado-says.html
Cia. Brasileira de Distribuicao
Group Pao de Acucar has partnered with builder Cyrela Brazil
Realty SA Empreendimentos & Participacoes to invest in real
estate in the city of  Sao Paulo , O Estado de S. Paulo reported,
citing Vice-President of Corporate Affairs Hugo Bethlem.  The companies, which are working alongside developer Thera,
plan to build a block of residential apartments and offices,
which will include a hotel, shop and Extra drugstore, according
to the newspaper. Pao de Acucar expects sales of the units to
generate a profit margin of at least 20 percent, O Estado said.  Pao de Acucar is planning two further real estate
partnerships in Sao Paulo this year and aims to open 300 new
Extra Facil stores between 2012 and 2014, O Estado said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karen Eeuwens in London at 
